to serve them.

205
00:15:39,718 --> 00:15:41,413
Now they won't listen to me.

206
00:15:41,588 --> 00:15:43,112
The war is long over.

207
00:15:43,289 --> 00:15:45,621
You and the other Priests
did your jobs.

208
00:15:45,692 --> 00:15:48,593
It's not over.
Not for me.

209
00:15:49,096 --> 00:15:52,862
You can't break your covenant to hunt
down a small group of scavengers.

210
00:15:52,968 --> 00:15:54,128
It would be sacrilege.

211
00:15:54,503 --> 00:15:55,936
I have to.

212
00:15:59,343 --> 00:16:00,708
That's what I was afraid of.

213
00:16:00,811 --> 00:16:01,861
(DOOR BANGING OPEN)

214
00:16:01,862 --> 00:16:04,880
GUARD 1: Move.
GUARD 2: Get out of the way.

215
00:16:04,883 --> 00:16:05,941
Stand back.

216
00:16:09,454 --> 00:16:13,891
If you go out there right now, you
risk stirring things up again.

217
00:16:15,461 --> 00:16:18,919
You have to look at the bigger picture.
It's for the greater good.

218
00:16:19,132 --> 00:16:21,498
Is this the world I fought for?

219
00:16:22,170 --> 00:16:23,220
No,

220
00:16:24,806 --> 00:16:26,797
but it's the only world
we have left.

221
00:16:28,443 --> 00:16:32,209
I'm begging you,
don't do anything foolish.

222
00:16:33,216 --> 00:16:35,150
Remember your vow,

223
00:16:35,218 --> 00:16:38,551
to go against the Church
is to go against God.

224
00:16:40,023 --> 00:16:41,854
Then I go against God.

225
00:16:53,941 --> 00:16:54,991
