Two.

252
00:20:42,612 --> 00:20:45,012
All right, all right!
All right!

253
00:20:45,315 --> 00:20:47,806
Goddamn son of a bitch!

254
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:51,853
Now, y'all listen up.

255
00:20:53,090 --> 00:20:55,786
This stuff is good for nothin'

256
00:20:55,788 --> 00:20:58,528
but linin' that man's pockets
with your hard-earned cash.

257
00:20:58,531 --> 00:21:00,941
VILLAGER: You don't know that.
You're just a kid.

258
00:21:00,967 --> 00:21:02,867
We gotta do somethin'
to keep us safe.

259
00:21:03,035 --> 00:21:04,468
Move out of the way!

260
00:21:06,507 --> 00:21:08,617
I don't blame any
of you for bein' scared,

261
00:21:09,878 --> 00:21:13,177
but the vampires are gone
and they're not comin' back.

262
00:21:21,525 --> 00:21:25,859
You'll have to excuse the attention.
Strangers aren't too common out here.

263
00:21:28,966 --> 00:21:30,956
Is it true what they say
about Priests?

264
00:21:31,904 --> 00:21:33,394
You wield the hand of God?

265
00:21:38,746 --> 00:21:40,008
How is he?

266
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:42,842
He's awake.

267
00:21:53,095 --> 00:21:55,689
The Clergy took away a boy

268
00:21:57,366 --> 00:21:59,698
and returned an old man.

269
00:22:03,241 --> 00:22:08,577
After the war was over, Shannon
figured you'd come back.

270
00:22:09,849 --> 00:22:11,282
I wanted to.

271
00:22:15,889 --> 00:22:17,550
Didn't seem right anymore.

272
00:22:18,358 --> 00:22:19,916
I couldn't save her.

273
00:22:22,064 --> 00:22:25,727
I tried, but I never
had your gift.

274
00:22:27,202 --> 00:22:29,796
You gave her a life
I no longer could.

275
00:22:30,573 --> 00:22:32,803
I will always be
grateful to you for that.

276
00:22:34,077 --> 00:22:38,480
Never a day went by when I didn't
wish she'd forget about you.

277
00:22:49,295 --> 00:22:51,229
You find Lucy.

278
00:22:51,932 --> 00:22:54,059
You bring her home safe.

279
00:22:55,102 --> 00:22:57,764
And you promise me
somethin', brother,

280
00:22:59,575 --> 00:23:01,008
kill 'em all.

281
00:23:05,681 --> 00:23:10,482
Most people out here know the Clergy think
of us as a bunch of godless heathens.

282
00:23:10,587 --> 00:23:12,316
And that's how we like it.

283
00:23:12,422 --> 00:23:15,312
It means they tend to keep their
noses out of our business.

284
00:23:15,926 --> 00:23:17,856
So you can imagine
how surprised I was

285
00:23:17,928 --> 00:23:20,863
when they contacted me
askin' if I'd seen you.

286
00:23:21,299 --> 00:23:25,099
Sayin' that anyone goin' after Lucy
is to be arrested immediately.

287
00:23:26,039 --> 00:23:28,872
Said she's in God's hands now.

288
00:23:29,543 --> 00:23:34,446
Problem is, we both know outside
of a week, Lucy will be dead.

289
00:23:34,615 --> 00:23:37,015
Or worse, infected.

290
00:23:37,619 --> 00:23:39,177
So with all due
respect to God...

291
00:23:49,734 --> 00:23:51,167
You're wasting your time.

292
00:23:51,703 --> 00:23:54,900
No, no, no, you are not
cutting me out of this.

293
00:23:55,007 --> 00:23:56,736
I am the one that
came and got you.

294
00:23:56,910 --> 00:24:00,038
People in this town don't think
you can keep them safe here.

295
00:24:02,183 --> 00:24:04,713
What makes you think
you'll do any good out there?

296
00:24:19,670 --> 00:24:21,103
You any good with a gun?

297
00:24:21,238 --> 00:24:22,830
Better than I am with a knife.

298
00:24:24,441 --> 00:24:25,669
We leave at dawn.

299
00:24:25,744 --> 00:24:27,006
All right.

300
00:24:29,247 --> 00:24:33,343
What's with all the bullets, anyways?
I thought Priests didn't use firearms.

301
00:24:33,519 --> 00:24:34,850
We don't.

302
00:24:36,222 --> 00:24:37,348
They're for you.

303
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:45,263
ORELAS: (ON PA)
God protects you.

304
00:24:45,266 --> 00:24:47,401
The Church protects you.

305
00:24:57,881 --> 00:25:00,941
ORELAS: You have been called
to serve once more.

306
00:25:01,317 --> 00:25:05,481
One of your own
has broken his sacred vow.

307
00:25:05,957 --> 00:25:08,585
His actions are a threat
to the entire Order.

308
00:25:10,496 --> 00:25:15,559
You will find him
and bring him back to me.

309
00:25:17,070 --> 00:25:19,004
Dead or alive.

310
00:25:27,081 --> 00:25:31,643
PREACHER: "And I will teach transgressors
your ways, and sinners will turn back to you.

311
00:25:31,822 --> 00:25:35,314
"Save me from bloodguilt,
O God, the God who saves me.

312
00:25:35,458 --> 00:25:38,518
"And my tongue will sing
of your righteousness.

313
00:25:38,663 --> 00:25:40,653
"And my mouth will
declare your praise.

314
00:25:41,032 --> 00:25:44,433
"You do not delight in
sacrifice or I would bring it.

315
00:25:44,603 --> 00:25:46,969
"You do not take pleasure
in burnt offerings."

316
00:26:11,301 --> 00:26:12,495
What is it?

317
00:26:12,803 --> 00:26:16,705
Vampire tracks are random.
Sets of two, three, four prints at a time.

318
00:26:16,809 --> 00:26:18,071
But these are two by two.

319
00:26:18,209 --> 00:26:20,177
It must have been
one of the Familiars.

320
00:26:20,380 --> 00:26:23,838
Vampires don't bring Familiars on the hunt.
They slow them down.

321
00:26:24,717 --> 00:26:26,150
No, this...

322
00:26:28,521 --> 00:26:30,318
This was something else.

323
00:26:31,893 --> 00:26:33,656
Tracks head north.

324
00:26:33,828 --> 00:26:35,728
There's a reservation
up that way.

325
00:26:35,897 --> 00:26:38,092
Well, then that's
where we start.

326
00:26:50,748 --> 00:26:54,912
Nightshade Reservation.
Nothin' but red-outs and rejects.

327
00:26:55,288 --> 00:26:56,755
They're a fallen tribe.

328
00:26:58,024 --> 00:27:00,788
Either way, we don't have
much time to get in and out.

329
00:27:15,811 --> 00:27:16,891
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

330
00:27:22,485 --> 00:27:24,146
No guards.

331
00:27:40,507 --> 00:27:42,600
I thought Familiars
were illegal.

332
00:27:42,777 --> 00:27:46,076
Nobody really enforces it.
So long as it's voluntary.

333
00:27:46,448 --> 00:27:47,813
PRIEST: Voluntary?

334
00:27:47,949 --> 00:27:52,079
HICKS: Yeah, they come from the fringes.
Drifters wantin' to get infected.

335
00:27:52,082 --> 00:27:56,923
I mean, becomin' a vampire slave
ain't my idea of belongin',

336
00:27:56,927 --> 00:27:59,191
but people get all
sorts of strange ideas.

337
00:27:59,329 --> 00:28:03,425
So long as they keep to themselves
it makes no difference to me.

338
00:28:22,456 --> 00:28:24,146
You're not welcome
here, Priest.

339
00:28:25,527 --> 00:28:27,222
These lands are protected.

340
00:28:28,131 --> 00:28:29,462
I got this.

341
00:28:31,735 --> 00:28:35,796
We're lookin' for a local girl kidnapped
about four nights ago by a vamp pack.

342
00:28:35,974 --> 00:28:37,407
Came through this way.

343
00:28:37,575 --> 00:28:40,009
Nobody comes
through Nightshade.

344
00:28:40,078 --> 00:28:42,842
That's the way
we like it. Nice

345
00:28:44,383 --> 00:28:45,850
and quiet.

346
00:28:46,719 --> 00:28:49,688
Good. I'm sure we won't
have any trouble.

347
00:29:32,975 --> 00:29:36,570
They excrete it.
Use it to build their hives.

348
00:29:59,072 --> 00:30:01,939
HICKS: I guess now we know
what happened to the guards.

349
00:30:03,410 --> 00:30:04,550
(METAL PANEL OPENING)

350
00:30:09,517 --> 00:30:10,567
(WHIMPERING)

351
00:30:10,569 --> 00:30:11,818
(EXCLAIMS IN DISGUST)

352
00:30:11,820 --> 00:30:13,082
No, no.

353
00:30:13,756 --> 00:30:16,020
You must go.
Master will be angry. Please.

354
00:30:16,259 --> 00:30:17,309
(SHUSHING)

355
00:30:19,463 --> 00:30:20,513
Where's the girl?

356
00:30:22,100 --> 00:30:24,810
I don't know what you're
talking about. Please. Please.

357
00:30:25,303 --> 00:30:28,329
Master doesn't feed on humans anymore.
See? See?

358
00:30:28,439 --> 00:30:29,879
Yeah, tell that to the guards.

359
00:30:32,612 --> 00:30:34,603
Where is she?
Please, don't.

360
00:30:34,713 --> 00:30:35,839
Where is she?

361
00:30:36,550 --> 00:30:37,600
(METAL SCRAPING)

362
00:30:41,221 --> 00:30:42,279
Shit.

363
00:30:47,663 --> 00:30:49,688
Priest! Priest!

364
00:30:59,077 --> 00:31:00,127
(YELLING)

365
00:31:03,214 --> 00:31:04,264
(PANTING)

366
00:31:12,458 --> 00:31:13,686
Save your bullets.

367
00:31:29,512 --> 00:31:30,562
(SCREAMING)

368
00:31:41,727 --> 00:31:43,752
Now we can do this
the easy way, or...

369
00:31:45,898 --> 00:31:46,956
Oh, good.

370
00:31:47,968 --> 00:31:49,902
I've always preferred
the hard way.

371
00:31:51,305 --> 00:31:52,935
Tell me where
they took the girl.

372
00:31:52,937 --> 00:31:54,906
Haven't you done
enough already, Priest?

373
00:31:54,909 --> 00:31:56,001
Tell me!

374
00:31:56,111 --> 00:31:58,636
Look around you.
Look what you've done to them.

375
00:31:58,747 --> 00:32:01,341
They once ruled this land.
They were warriors.

376
00:32:01,483 --> 00:32:03,610
They were gods.
They were murderers.

377
00:32:03,686 --> 00:32:07,417
They were what nature made
them to be. Just like you.

378
00:32:07,924 --> 00:32:10,017
You got 10 seconds
to start talking.

379
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:16,329
Ten seconds is all I need.

380
00:32:16,735 --> 00:32:17,935
You're too late, Priest.

381
00:32:18,837 --> 00:32:20,896
This is their time now.

382
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:28,509
They get your gun arm?

383
00:32:28,816 --> 00:32:29,908
Why?

384
00:32:30,451 --> 00:32:32,146
You're gonna need it.

385
00:32:58,818 --> 00:33:00,138
(MAKING CLICKING SOUNDS)

386
00:33:01,555 --> 00:33:03,425
(RESPONDING WITH
CLICKING SOUNDS)

387
00:33:07,462 --> 00:33:12,365
"Yea, though I walk through the valley of the
shadow of death, I will fear no evil..."

388
00:33:12,369 --> 00:33:14,502
Your words mean
nothing to them, Priest.

389
00:33:14,504 --> 00:33:16,233
"...for thou art with me."

390
00:33:50,112 --> 00:33:51,204
Focus!

391
00:34:04,596 --> 00:34:05,646
(CALLING)

392
00:34:15,310 --> 00:34:16,470
Should we go after him?

393
00:34:16,644 --> 00:34:18,771
No need.
He'll die at first light.

394
00:34:19,113 --> 00:34:23,072
No more masters.
Just you and me.

395
00:34:26,989 --> 00:34:28,718
Tell me where
they took the girl.

396
00:34:29,226 --> 00:34:32,457
West. They took her west.
Why?

397
00:34:33,464 --> 00:34:35,955
You have no idea
what's coming, Priest.

398
00:34:36,334 --> 00:34:37,384
(ROARING)

399
00:34:53,220 --> 00:34:54,270
(VAMPIRE GROWLING)

400
00:34:58,660 --> 00:34:59,740
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

401
00:35:09,408 --> 00:35:12,502
PRIEST: The Familiar said
they traveled west from here.

402
00:35:14,947 --> 00:35:16,710
Sola Mira.

403
00:35:17,416 --> 00:35:18,610
A hive?

404
00:35:18,917 --> 00:35:20,214
One of the largest.

405
00:35:20,216 --> 00:35:23,387
But I thought all the hives
were liquidated after the war.

406
00:35:23,390 --> 00:35:24,516
They were.

407
00:35:25,526 --> 00:35:27,858
That's why we need to go look.

408
00:35:27,928 --> 00:35:31,022
There were more than
50 crypts in this reservation,

409
00:35:31,099 --> 00:35:33,260
but only six vampires left.

410
00:35:33,603 --> 00:35:34,865
The weak.

411
00:35:35,972 --> 00:35:37,405
The left-behind.

412
00:35:37,774 --> 00:35:39,765
We find the missing,
we'll find Lucy.

413
00:35:46,718 --> 00:35:48,777
I may not have seen the war,

414
00:35:49,588 --> 00:35:52,887
but I know the look a man
gets when he likes killing.

415
00:35:54,093 --> 00:35:56,118
It comes easy to you.

416
00:35:59,299 --> 00:36:00,926
It just comes.

417
00:36:02,737 --> 00:36:05,103
Easy's got nothing
to do with it.

418
00:36:08,611 --> 00:36:10,135
Give me your gun.

419
00:36:10,812 --> 00:36:11,862
What?

420
00:36:12,682 --> 00:36:14,309
Give me your gun.

421
00:36:19,490 --> 00:36:21,651
Vampires don't move
like humans.

422
00:36:23,595 --> 00:36:26,425
Their body weight pulls them
into concentric patterns.

423
00:36:30,137 --> 00:36:33,087
You need to anticipate their
trajectory to get a kill shot.

424
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,880
Are you teaching me to shoot?

425
00:36:34,976 --> 00:36:36,906
I'm teaching you
how to kill vampires.

426
00:36:37,878 --> 00:36:41,780
There are always
two points, A and B.

427
00:36:42,717 --> 00:36:45,618
Know them both,
and you'll kill a vampire.

428
00:36:58,337 --> 00:37:01,397
A man came aboard,
says he has something for you.

429
00:37:07,981 --> 00:37:09,031
You

430
00:37:10,251 --> 00:37:13,743
told me to come
if I had any information.

431
00:37:13,887 --> 00:37:18,187
But before I tell you,
and I hate to bring this up,

432
00:37:18,494 --> 00:37:23,193
but there is this small
little matter of compensation.

433
00:37:24,268 --> 00:37:27,760
Now, you've been
really good for business

434
00:37:28,038 --> 00:37:31,667
so I am more than willing
to cut you a deal.

435
00:37:32,945 --> 00:37:35,607
I can smell the blood
running through your veins.

436
00:37:36,282 --> 00:37:37,442
Smells like

437
00:37:37,850 --> 00:37:38,900
dinner.

438
00:37:39,952 --> 00:37:41,385
Okay. All right.

439
00:37:43,456 --> 00:37:48,519
After you snatched the girl, a couple
of nights later, a Priest showed up.

440
00:37:48,596 --> 00:37:49,646
A Priest?

441
00:37:51,098 --> 00:37:54,898
And he was with this sheriff.
A real hard case.

442
00:37:54,970 --> 00:37:57,768
He run me out of town before
I could make a single sale.

443
00:37:59,376 --> 00:38:00,468
You've done well.

444
00:38:01,145 --> 00:38:02,476
Thank you.

445
00:38:06,750 --> 00:38:07,800
(GASPING)

446
00:38:19,166 --> 00:38:21,156
BLACK HAT:
There's your compensation.

447
00:38:22,403 --> 00:38:23,927
Put him to work.

448
00:38:59,979 --> 00:39:01,029
(DEVICE BEEPING)

449
00:39:09,658 --> 00:39:12,248
HICKS: I used to ride out here
a lot when I was little.

450
00:39:13,196 --> 00:39:14,823
Stare at all this stuff.

451
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:17,861
Wonder what it used to be.

452
00:39:19,805 --> 00:39:23,866
After a while,
it just made my eyes ache.

453
00:39:27,212 --> 00:39:28,372
Did Owen know?

454
00:39:29,214 --> 00:39:31,011
About you and Lucy?

455
00:39:37,225 --> 00:39:38,317
No.

456
00:39:39,694 --> 00:39:40,786
No.

457
00:39:41,463 --> 00:39:43,397
She wanted to tell him,

458
00:39:43,632 --> 00:39:48,569
but Owen wasn't the easiest
man to talk to.

459
00:39:50,140 --> 00:39:54,543
Besides, he was so focused on his work,
there wasn't much room for anything else.

460
00:39:57,148 --> 00:39:58,376
Do you love her?

461
00:40:03,556 --> 00:40:04,606
(SIGHING)

462
00:40:10,531 --> 00:40:12,726
You know, if she's infected,

463
00:40:15,704 --> 00:40:17,228
I'll kill her.

464
00:40:21,710 --> 00:40:23,268
You'll try,

465
00:40:24,714 --> 00:40:26,682
but you won't be able to.

466
00:40:28,052 --> 00:40:31,954
I wasn't there to protect her once, I
won't make that same mistake again.

467
00:40:37,296 --> 00:40:38,346
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

468
00:41:38,502 --> 00:41:40,527
Feels like our grave.

469
00:41:41,138 --> 00:41:42,196
It's a trap.

470
00:41:42,840 --> 00:41:43,890
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

471
00:41:50,649 --> 00:41:53,379
This is a waste of time.
There's nothing here.

472
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:55,210
Stay here.

473
00:41:55,622 --> 00:41:58,716
Anything comes up
that isn't me, shoot it.

474
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:06,160
Great.

475
00:43:15,383 --> 00:43:16,433
(GRUNTING)

476
00:43:31,904 --> 00:43:33,166
What are you doing here?

477
00:43:33,439 --> 00:43:35,839
The Clergy sent me.
Ordered me to bring you back.

478
00:43:36,141 --> 00:43:37,281
(PRIESTESS GRUNTING)

479
00:43:38,110 --> 00:43:41,807
They sent four of us to track you.
We split up at Nightshade.

480
00:43:41,882 --> 00:43:44,282
I rode out here hoping
to get ahead of you.

481
00:43:45,453 --> 00:43:47,478
The others went on to Jericho.

482
00:43:47,480 --> 00:43:51,891
I didn't believe it when they
told me you broke your vow.

483
00:43:51,894 --> 00:43:53,486
They left me no choice.

484
00:43:53,662 --> 00:43:55,527
(GUNSHOT) Hicks!

485
00:43:56,900 --> 00:43:58,561
What the hell is that thing?

486
00:43:59,336 --> 00:44:00,776
PRIEST: It's a Hive Guardian.

487
00:44:01,173 --> 00:44:02,223
Who the hell are you?

488
00:44:02,224 --> 00:44:06,141
It's too big to get down here, which
is the only reason you're still alive.

489
00:44:06,143 --> 00:44:07,235
Who the hell is that?

490
00:44:08,146 --> 00:44:09,238
You ready?

491
00:44:15,556 --> 00:44:16,606
(GROWLING)

492
00:44:17,991 --> 00:44:19,041
(ROARING)

493
00:44:36,046 --> 00:44:37,096
PRIESTESS: Hey!

494
00:45:55,341 --> 00:45:56,391
Not bad.

495
00:46:00,078 --> 00:46:01,128
(GUNSHOT)

496
00:46:03,984 --> 00:46:07,681
Point A, meet point fucking B.

497
00:46:07,956 --> 00:46:11,746
The hive's been abandoned for years.
Why would something be protecting it?

498
00:46:14,749 --> 00:46:20,162
Does the lawman know what
you'll do if she's infected?

499
00:46:17,166 --> 00:46:18,531
He knows.

500
00:46:18,802 --> 00:46:20,394
He'll try to stop you.

501
00:46:21,238 --> 00:46:22,796
He won't be able to.

502
00:46:27,411 --> 00:46:29,504
It's been hard all these years.

503
00:46:30,349 --> 00:46:33,011
Not seeing the others.
Not talking.

504
00:46:34,586 --> 00:46:37,056
Sector Seven was the only
place I could find work.

505
00:46:37,757 --> 00:46:39,554
Waste management.

506
00:46:40,093 --> 00:46:41,651
No one would hire me.

507
00:46:42,497 --> 00:46:44,192
"No applicable skills."

508
00:46:44,366 --> 00:46:45,924
I heard that, too.

509
00:46:49,004 --> 00:46:51,336
I didn't come here
to bring you back.

510
00:46:52,341 --> 00:46:53,672
I came here to warn you.

511
00:46:59,182 --> 00:47:02,549
There are nights when I wake up

512
00:47:04,188 --> 00:47:06,713
and I think I'm back
on the front lines.

513
00:47:09,128 --> 00:47:14,464
I'm sweating, my muscles are clenched
like I'm ready for something.

514
00:47:16,370 --> 00:47:18,895
Nights like that,
I don't go back to sleep.

515
00:47:20,075 --> 00:47:21,975
I have bad dreams.

516
00:47:23,077 --> 00:47:24,544
Me, too.

517
00:47:30,620 --> 00:47:32,417
There are other nights.

518
00:47:33,057 --> 00:47:34,649
The good nights.

519
00:47:35,592 --> 00:47:37,116
I dream about other things.

520
00:47:55,398 --> 00:47:57,515
HICKS: Why doesn't it look
like the rest of the hive?

521
00:47:57,819 --> 00:48:01,311
PRIESTESS: This section's new.
They must have rebuilt it.

522
00:48:15,440 --> 00:48:17,203
HICKS: My God.

523
00:48:21,146 --> 00:48:23,171
They bred a new army.

524
00:48:25,284 --> 00:48:26,546
Where did they all go?

525
00:48:26,853 --> 00:48:27,903
(BATS CHIRPING)

526
00:48:32,794 --> 00:48:34,557
Only one way to find out.

527
00:48:42,239 --> 00:48:45,640
Um... Are Priests allowed
to have relations?

528
00:48:45,709 --> 00:48:47,404
We take a vow of celibacy.

529
00:48:47,711 --> 00:48:49,679
So you mean, you've never...

530
00:48:49,813 --> 00:48:52,145
I was a young girl
when the Clergy found me.

531
00:48:52,850 --> 00:48:53,908
What about him?

532
00:48:56,522 --> 00:48:58,632
PRIESTESS: His talents
developed later.

533
00:48:58,724 --> 00:49:01,386
He was nearly your age
when the Clergy came for him.

534
00:49:02,328 --> 00:49:04,498
That made his sacrifice
greater than most.

535
00:49:06,535 --> 00:49:08,400
The air is changing.

536
00:49:10,739 --> 00:49:12,549
PRIEST: Well,
there's your answer.

537
00:49:12,551 --> 00:49:14,074
They dug right through
the mountain,

538
00:49:14,075 --> 00:49:16,771
made a hole big enough
to fit an army through.

539
00:49:18,748 --> 00:49:20,375
What town is that?

540
00:49:21,284 --> 00:49:22,683
It's Jericho.

541
00:49:23,921 --> 00:49:25,611
Where'd you say
the others went?

542
00:49:33,666 --> 00:49:34,716
(RUMBLING)

543
00:49:35,268 --> 00:49:36,318
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

544
00:49:42,142 --> 00:49:43,234
What the hell?

545
00:50:07,373 --> 00:50:08,423
(GASPING)

546
00:50:11,811 --> 00:50:12,891
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

547
00:50:33,036 --> 00:50:34,264
Hello?

548
00:50:42,381 --> 00:50:43,643
Hello?

549
00:50:51,825 --> 00:50:53,520
Is anybody there?

550
00:51:13,317 --> 00:51:14,451
Let's begin.

551
00:51:14,852 --> 00:51:16,172
(OPERATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

552
00:51:25,398 --> 00:51:26,448
(POUNDING)

553
00:51:32,641 --> 00:51:33,691
(HEAVY RUMBLING)

554
00:51:47,691 --> 00:51:48,851
I don't see anything.

555
00:51:53,165 --> 00:51:54,215
(SCREAMING)

556
00:51:57,103 --> 00:51:59,273
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)
(VAMPIRES GROWLING)

557
00:52:39,286 --> 00:52:40,336
(YELLING)

558
00:52:46,996 --> 00:52:48,046
(GROANING)

559
00:52:59,976 --> 00:53:03,036
Brothers, you have a choice.

560
00:53:03,648 --> 00:53:06,208
You could follow
in my footsteps,

561
00:53:06,652 --> 00:53:08,347
or you can follow in his.

562
00:53:28,744 --> 00:53:30,336
We're too late.

563
00:53:30,647 --> 00:53:31,705
We separate.

564
00:53:32,816 --> 00:53:35,580
PRIEST: Go through each
building, see what we find.

565
00:54:25,746 --> 00:54:26,796
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

566
00:54:58,284 --> 00:54:59,664
HICKS: There's nobody left.

567
00:55:00,354 --> 00:55:01,685
Not a soul.

568
00:55:03,090 --> 00:55:04,819
Too many mouths to feed.

569
00:55:36,631 --> 00:55:38,191
HICKS: Killing three Priests?

570
00:55:38,466 --> 00:55:41,128
What kind of vampire
could do something like that?

571
00:55:42,304 --> 00:55:44,534
Nothing we've ever seen before.

572
00:55:45,874 --> 00:55:49,810
HICKS: How could they take an entire
town overnight and vanish by sunrise?

573
00:55:49,878 --> 00:55:53,575
There are no other hives
around here. No reservations.

574
00:56:03,762 --> 00:56:05,572
PRIEST: Where's
this rail line go?

575
00:56:05,831 --> 00:56:07,389
It's an old mining line.

576
00:56:07,533 --> 00:56:10,434
It starts in the Dunkirk Mines
above Augustine.

577
00:56:10,604 --> 00:56:13,437
Jericho's the last stop before it reaches...
The Cities.

578
00:56:14,241 --> 00:56:17,074
Heading back to the Cities
would be suicide, right?

579
00:56:17,178 --> 00:56:18,270
The sun will kill 'em.

580
00:56:18,846 --> 00:56:21,041
There is no sun in the Cities.

581
00:56:22,016 --> 00:56:23,381
Not anymore.

582
00:56:24,620 --> 00:56:26,451
Without us,
they're defenseless.

583
00:56:29,460 --> 00:56:30,893
I'm responsible.

584
00:56:30,961 --> 00:56:32,724
No. This was systematic.

585
00:56:33,230 --> 00:56:36,840
Whoever took Lucy knew that you'd come
for her and that we'd come for you.

586
00:56:36,902 --> 00:56:38,130
They were drawing us out.

587
00:56:38,132 --> 00:56:40,805
They must have been picking up
different factions along the way.

588
00:56:40,806 --> 00:56:43,138
Moving during the day
and feeding at night.

589
00:56:43,443 --> 00:56:44,876
It's going to be a massacre.

590
00:56:45,144 --> 00:56:47,078
It's gonna be a war.

591
00:56:48,147 --> 00:56:50,445
A train carrying
an army of vampire?

592
00:56:51,953 --> 00:56:54,820
What chance do we have of
stopping something like that?

593
00:56:54,822 --> 00:56:59,925
I'll overtake the train, blow the rail line.
You two get aboard, find Lucy.

594
00:56:59,929 --> 00:57:01,760
I'll start charging the bikes.

595
00:57:01,997 --> 00:57:06,147
It's gonna take everything we have to stop
that train before it reaches the Cities.

596
00:57:13,911 --> 00:57:17,472
BLACK HAT: You must be starving.
You haven't eaten in days.

597
00:57:19,585 --> 00:57:23,282
Have you ever had
real roast duck?

598
00:57:24,924 --> 00:57:29,258
It's very rare.
Very exotic.

599
00:57:31,466 --> 00:57:32,831
Of course not.

600
00:57:33,668 --> 00:57:36,637
Try it. You'll never
have better.

601
00:57:40,676 --> 00:57:41,938
What do you want?

602
00:57:42,780 --> 00:57:45,442
I want the same things
that you want.

603
00:57:46,451 --> 00:57:50,319
I want to be free from a life
of suffering and sacrifice.

604
00:57:50,955 --> 00:57:55,551
To no longer be told that
your every desire is a sin.

605
00:57:56,162 --> 00:57:57,823
I mean, after all

606
00:57:58,231 --> 00:58:02,133
if you're not committing sin,
you're not having fun.

607
00:58:12,381 --> 00:58:13,431
What are you?

608
00:58:15,985 --> 00:58:20,081
The Church teaches us that the
eyes are the windows to the soul.

609
00:58:20,591 --> 00:58:24,049
And that since vampire
evolved without eyes,

610
00:58:24,329 --> 00:58:27,196
it is a soulless creature to be

611
00:58:28,201 --> 00:58:29,532
eradicated.

612
00:58:30,670 --> 00:58:33,104
And I have seen
the soul of the vampire,

613
00:58:33,739 --> 00:58:37,698
and let me tell you, it is far
more pure than that of any man.

614
00:58:39,379 --> 00:58:41,370
Now you ask me what I am.

615
00:58:44,086 --> 00:58:46,384
I am the bringer of the tide.

616
00:58:47,289 --> 00:58:50,918
I am the wave that will wash
clean this unclean world.

617
00:58:52,562 --> 00:58:54,757
And you and your

618
00:58:55,967 --> 00:58:58,959
Priest will help me do it.

619
00:59:03,275 --> 00:59:05,470
He's gonna kill her, isn't he?

620
00:59:06,078 --> 00:59:07,636
If she's infected.

621
00:59:14,321 --> 00:59:15,811
She talked about him.

622
00:59:16,324 --> 00:59:17,764
Said she never got to know him.

623
00:59:19,095 --> 00:59:20,585
She wanted to.

624
00:59:21,664 --> 00:59:24,633
What kind of man would kill
his own flesh and blood?

625
00:59:25,101 --> 00:59:28,161
If she becomes a Familiar, she's
no one's flesh and blood.

626
00:59:30,040 --> 00:59:31,166
Not anymore.

627
01:00:12,223 --> 01:00:13,918
I've held on to it

628
01:00:14,392 --> 01:00:16,019
all these years.

629
01:00:17,496 --> 01:00:20,556
To remind me of everything
they stripped away from us.

630
01:00:21,335 --> 01:00:24,395
Our honor, our abilities,
our faith.

631
01:00:26,506 --> 01:00:31,102
Today, when we ride, I want you to remember
our power doesn't come from the Church.

632
01:00:31,212 --> 01:00:32,873
It comes from God.

633
01:00:44,128 --> 01:00:45,595
With or without the Clergy,

634
01:00:46,230 --> 01:00:48,130
we're still Priests.

635
01:01:07,590 --> 01:01:08,640
(SHIVERS)

636
01:01:10,059 --> 01:01:11,424
I can't.

637
01:01:23,106 --> 01:01:25,597
When I heard
what happened to Shannon,

638
01:01:26,577 --> 01:01:28,943
I prayed for her salvation

639
01:01:30,817 --> 01:01:32,444
and then I prayed for mine.

640
01:01:33,954 --> 01:01:36,616
Because in the darkness
of my heart,

641
01:01:37,124 --> 01:01:41,652
I hoped her death
would free you at last.

642
01:02:24,313 --> 01:02:25,363
(GUN COCKING)

643
01:02:27,317 --> 01:02:29,080
Tell me you won't kill her.

644
01:02:29,252 --> 01:02:31,049
Hicks, don't do this.

645
01:02:31,155 --> 01:02:33,487
Tell me, or I will shoot
you where you stand.

646
01:02:33,490 --> 01:02:37,560
It would be easier to face your bullet
here than to face what might lie ahead.

647
01:02:37,563 --> 01:02:38,655
Why do you even care?

648
01:02:38,898 --> 01:02:40,708
She is nothing
but a stranger to you.

649
01:02:47,039 --> 01:02:48,097
She's his daughter.

650
01:02:50,377 --> 01:02:52,487
She was just a baby
when the Clergy took me.

651
01:02:52,747 --> 01:02:54,908
You're lying. I knew Owen.

652
01:02:55,016 --> 01:02:57,211
The child needed a father.

653
01:02:58,354 --> 01:02:59,946
We all made sacrifices.

654
01:03:05,396 --> 01:03:06,454
Hicks,

655
01:03:08,967 --> 01:03:10,457
if you do this,

656
01:03:11,804 --> 01:03:14,272
it won't matter
if you find Lucy.

657
01:03:15,406 --> 01:03:19,399
You won't stop the train, and
you won't be able to save her.

658
01:03:22,048 --> 01:03:23,310
You won't save her.

659
01:03:34,330 --> 01:03:36,080
We ride out
and meet this together.

660
01:03:54,754 --> 01:03:59,157
When the time comes, you blow the
tracks, then you get out of there!

661
01:03:59,293 --> 01:04:01,043
What if you're still
on the train?

662
01:04:10,639 --> 01:04:11,697
Good luck.

663
01:04:28,794 --> 01:04:29,852
Focus.

664
01:05:16,685 --> 01:05:17,735
(SCREAMING)

665
01:05:25,929 --> 01:05:26,979
Shit.

666
01:05:53,462 --> 01:05:55,987
Shit. Shit.
(VAMPIRE GROWLING SOFTLY)

667
01:05:56,799 --> 01:05:57,993
Shit.

668
01:06:06,744 --> 01:06:08,143
Hello, my friend.

669
01:06:30,172 --> 01:06:32,140
You fell!
You let go.

670
01:06:33,476 --> 01:06:34,534
No!

671
01:06:35,211 --> 01:06:36,531
In the depths of that hive,

672
01:06:37,047 --> 01:06:40,949
I crossed the threshold
between life and death.

673
01:06:41,185 --> 01:06:42,846
And do you know what I found?

674
01:06:45,556 --> 01:06:49,458
The Queen we had come to kill,
my angel of mercy,

675
01:06:51,464 --> 01:06:55,457
she turned me into something that
had never existed in this world,

676
01:06:57,570 --> 01:06:59,731
a human vampire.

677
01:07:01,910 --> 01:07:03,002
Join me.

678
01:07:03,378 --> 01:07:05,573
Accept the blood of the Queen,

679
01:07:05,680 --> 01:07:10,811
and together, we can return
to the Cities as brothers.

680
01:07:11,821 --> 01:07:13,345
Where's my daughter?

681
01:07:14,357 --> 01:07:16,348
Waiting for your decision.

682
01:07:26,572 --> 01:07:27,622
(EXCLAIMING)

683
01:07:36,785 --> 01:07:38,218
You can't win.

684
01:07:38,553 --> 01:07:40,953
I'm stronger now
than you ever were.

685
01:07:50,869 --> 01:07:51,919
(BEEPING)

686
01:08:24,274 --> 01:08:25,324
(GRUNTING)

687
01:08:50,038 --> 01:08:51,088
(SCREAMING)

688
01:09:34,091 --> 01:09:35,141
(YELLING)

689
01:09:42,267 --> 01:09:43,317
(PANTING)

690
01:10:10,768 --> 01:10:13,293
This is your
last chance, Priest.

691
01:10:14,037 --> 01:10:15,937
The Queen's hands
have not been idle.

692
01:10:16,040 --> 01:10:19,100
Mankind will find no quarter
from what's coming.

693
01:10:19,276 --> 01:10:20,607
Join me,

694
01:10:20,978 --> 01:10:24,243
and your life of
sacrifice will be over.

695
01:10:24,482 --> 01:10:25,813
Never.

696
01:10:27,186 --> 01:10:28,236
(SCREAMING)

697
01:10:34,128 --> 01:10:35,178
(GRUNTING)

698
01:11:17,480 --> 01:11:18,530
Shit.

699
01:11:26,657 --> 01:11:27,954
LUCY: Hicks!

700
01:11:28,493 --> 01:11:29,543
Lucy!

701
01:11:42,742 --> 01:11:43,834
Shit.

702
01:11:44,411 --> 01:11:45,537
Did you find her?

703
01:11:45,713 --> 01:11:48,477
I couldn't get close.
They took her to the front.

704
01:12:09,107 --> 01:12:11,234
You would have made
a good Priest.

705
01:12:12,111 --> 01:12:13,339
Thanks.

706
01:12:13,512 --> 01:12:15,673
Don't let it go to your head.

707
01:12:25,527 --> 01:12:26,858
Hicks!
Lucy!

708
01:12:31,801 --> 01:12:32,859
No!

709
01:12:38,975 --> 01:12:40,025
(GROANING)

710
01:12:52,793 --> 01:12:54,090
Stop it!

711
01:12:54,995 --> 01:12:56,724
No!

712
01:13:03,338 --> 01:13:04,498
No, Lucy!

713
01:13:05,640 --> 01:13:07,335
Very good.
You're fast.

714
01:13:08,110 --> 01:13:09,236
Just like your father.

715
01:13:13,917 --> 01:13:14,975
He never told you.

716
01:13:26,867 --> 01:13:27,917
(SCREAMING)

717
01:13:49,794 --> 01:13:51,159
Burn.

718
01:14:00,406 --> 01:14:03,068
In this time of need,
strengthen me.

719
01:14:07,148 --> 01:14:10,413
You are my refuge and strength.

720
01:14:10,518 --> 01:14:13,715
I do not fear,
for you are with me.

721
01:14:37,883 --> 01:14:38,933
(GRUNTING)

722
01:15:23,370 --> 01:15:24,420
(LUCY SCREAMING)

723
01:15:31,580 --> 01:15:32,740
I won't let you go!

724
01:15:39,524 --> 01:15:41,185
Your faith has failed you.

725
01:15:51,004 --> 01:15:52,596
(BEEPING)

726
01:15:56,043 --> 01:15:57,670
No!

727
01:16:04,887 --> 01:16:06,817
(PRIEST GRUNTING)
(LUCY SCREAMING)

728
01:16:10,127 --> 01:16:11,177
(SCREAMING)

729
01:16:21,773 --> 01:16:22,823
(PANTING)

730
01:16:56,982 --> 01:16:58,362
(MOTORCYCLE APPROACHING)

731
01:17:57,855 --> 01:17:58,905
(SIZZLING)

732
01:18:08,533 --> 01:18:12,697
"For the life of the flesh
is in the blood

733
01:18:13,172 --> 01:18:16,198
"and I have given it
to you upon the altar

734
01:18:16,776 --> 01:18:20,542
"to make an atonement
for your souls."

735
01:18:22,216 --> 01:18:23,656
(CONGREGATION CHATTERING)

736
01:18:34,331 --> 01:18:38,631
How dare you come back
to this holy place.

737
01:18:39,403 --> 01:18:44,033
A man who would defy the Church
for his own selfish crusade!

738
01:18:50,416 --> 01:18:51,542
(ALL GASPING)

739
01:18:58,927 --> 01:19:01,937
Look inside the burning train
just beyond these City walls

740
01:19:03,900 --> 01:19:05,710
you'll find hundreds
more like it,

741
01:19:07,011 --> 01:19:09,002
and their Queen
was not among them.

742
01:19:09,005 --> 01:19:10,063
Lies!

743
01:19:10,941 --> 01:19:13,068
This man is a charlatan.

744
01:19:13,543 --> 01:19:16,535
A risk to the security
of the Cities.

745
01:19:17,783 --> 01:19:20,752
There is no vampire menace.

746
01:19:20,920 --> 01:19:23,514
The war is over, Priest!

747
01:19:23,589 --> 01:19:26,524
No, it's just beginning.

748
01:19:39,708 --> 01:19:41,039
I've notified the others.

749
01:19:41,277 --> 01:19:43,627
We'll meet you at the
rendezvous in City Seven.

750
01:19:46,049 --> 01:19:47,209
Godspeed.